        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">The production volume of dichloropropene is calculated from the global production of allyl chloride, in which dichloropropene is a byproduct. For 1 kg of allyl chloride, 0.113 kg dichloropropene are produced (see dataset "allyl chloride production".
550000000 kg of allyl chloride are produced annually. Data retrived from "Acute exposure guideines level (AEGLs) FOR ALLYL CHLORIDE 107-05-1" (EPA, 2008) . Document refers to data from 1993(http://www.epa.gov/oppt/aegl/pubs/allyl_chloride.pdf, accessed 20150928)

The main use of dichloropropene is as pesticide. Much smaller quantities are used as solvent and chemical intermediate.   (http://www.atsdr.cdc.gov/toxprofiles/tp40.pdf). It is therefore assumed that 80% is used as a pesticide.</productionVolumeComment>
